sentences: He eventually moved to Nashville, Tennessee, where, in 1945, he became involved in Acuff-Rose Music, a music publishing house established by his father and his father's partner, Roy Acuff.
Following his father's death in 1954, Rose served as the company's president.
In 1985, he and partner Roy Acuff sold the Acuff-Rose catalogues to Gaylord Broadcasting Company.
In 1986, Rose joined his father as an inductee in the Country Music Hall of Fame.
